        {
            "title": "Grigor McClelland Doctoral Dissertation Award 2017 - Honourable Mention",
            "description": "The Grigor McClelland Doctoral Dissertation Award is an annual prize awarded to innovative scholarship demonstrated within a PhD thesis within management and organisation studies. The award is supported by the Journal of Management Studies (JMS) and the Society for the Advancement of Management Studies (SAMS). The Grigor McClelland Doctoral Dissertation Award aims to promote and recognize innovative PhD research in management and organization studies. The Award does not specify any preference towards topics or methods; its primary focus is to recognize and award doctoral research that is expansive and imaginative in that it covers significantly new terrain or counters existing thinking within management and organisational research. Grigor McClelland was the founder of SAMS, the founding editor of JMS, and the founding Director of Manchester Business School.",
