        {
            "title": "FSW Dissertation Award 2016",
            "description": "Best dissertation of 2016 in the Faculty of Social Science, VU University Amsterdam\n\n'The attractiveness of Jeroen Wolbers\u2019 study of cross-boundary coordination in disaster management is the clear position he has taken on. He argues on the basis of an impressive multimethod research that central coordination of emergency processes is never entirely feasible, his on sight observations reveal that fragmented coordination turns out to work more efficiently'.",
